  "local_port": 59288,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good online interior design courses?",
  "response": "There are several excellent online interior design courses that cater to different skill levels, from beginners to advanced designers. Here are some highly recommended options:\n\n1. **Coursera - Interior Design Specialization by CalArts**\n   - **Provider:** California Institute of the Arts\n   - **Description:** This specialization offers a comprehensive introduction to interior design, covering fundamental principles, space planning, and material selection.\n   - **Duration:** Approximately 6 months (3 hours/week)\n   - **Link:** [Coursera - Interior Design Specialization](https://www.coursera.org/specializations/interior-design)\n\n2. **Udemy - Interior Design for Beginners: Perfectly Style a Room in 7 Steps**\n   - **Provider:** Udemy\n   - **Description:** This beginner-friendly course focuses on the basics of styling a room, including color theory, furniture arrangement, and accessory selection.\n   - **Duration:** 3 hours on-demand video\n   - **Link:** [Udemy - Interior Design for Beginners](https://www.udemy.com/course/interior-design-for-beginners/)\n\n3. **Skillshare - Interior Design: Transform Your Home with Light and Shadow**\n   - **Provider:** Skillshare\n   - **Description:** This course teaches how to use light and shadow effectively to create mood and enhance spaces.\n   - **Duration:** 1 hour 20 minutes\n   - **Link:** [Skillshare - Interior Design with Light and Shadow](https://www.skillshare.com)\n\n4. **The New York Institute of Art and Design - Online Interior Design Course**\n   - **Provider:** NYIAD\n   - **Description:** This comprehensive course covers all aspects of interior design, from conceptualizing ideas to executing design plans. It includes assignments and personalized instructor feedback.\n   - **Duration:** Self-paced\n   - **Link:** [NYIAD - Online Interior Design Course](https://www.nyiad.edu/courses/interior-design)\n\n5. **MasterClass - Kelly Wearstler Teaches Interior Design**\n   - **Provider:** MasterClass\n   - **Description:** Renowned interior designer Kelly Wearstler shares her design philosophy, creative process, and professional insights.\n   - **Duration:** 2 hours 22 minutes\n   - **Link:** [MasterClass - Kelly Wearstler Teaches Interior Design](https://www.masterclass.com/classes/kelly-wearstler-teaches-interior-design)\n\n6. **Harvard University Extension School - Principles of Design for Residential Interiors**\n   - **Provider:** Harvard University\n   - **Description:** This course offers an in-depth look at the principles of residential interior design, including space planning, color theory, and material selection.\n   - **Duration:** 12 weeks (part-time)\n   - **Link:** [Harvard Extension School - Principles of Design](https://extension.harvard.edu)\n\n7. **The Interior Design Institute - Online Interior Design Course**\n   - **Provider:** The Interior Design Institute\n   - **Description:** This course provides a thorough grounding in interior design principles, practical design skills, and professional practices.\n   - **Duration:** 12 modules, self-paced\n   - **Link:** [The Interior Design Institute](https://www.theinteriordesigninstitute.com)\n\nEach of these courses offers unique insights and skills, so choosing the right one depends on your specific goals and level of experience.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
